description:
In a garden where drones bloom instead of roses, she stands—a spectral sentinel, born of ink, decay, and desire. Stained and smudged, she is both archive and apparition, listening as drones murmur above. She exists in ink, code, and sound. Matter. Memory. Motion

"Nymphe d’Encre sous Surveillance" is a 1/1 AI-Trained Ink Intervention from The Drones of Suburbia (Paris) by Miss AL Simpson—bridging the analogue with the algorithmic.

Offered as a threefold artefact:

– Memory — the NFT itself, an immutable on-chain record of resistance and beauty;

– Motion — a downloadable WAV of Cryptomusic: ambient, cinematic, composed by AI, and made to haunt the silence of surveillance;

– Matter - Signed A2 Print. Each NFT is paired with a signed A2 Print on Hahnemühle Photo Rag Metallic Paper.
